id: pm-m8yl
title: "CodeFactor/Maintainability: fix unsafe optional chaining (no-unsafe-optional-chaining ×25)"
description: "**Rule:** ESLint core `no-unsafe-optional-chaining` (CodeFactor message: \"Unsafe usage of optional chaining.\", category label \"Optional chaining with invalid undefined usage\"). **Count:** 25 (Maintainability, Minor).\n\n**CodeFactor list:** https://www.codefactor.io/repository/github/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/main?category=Maintainability&groupId=8467\n\n## What it is\n\nA `?.` short-circuits to `undefined`. Using that result in a position where `undefined` would throw or coerce incorrectly is flagged — e.g. property access / call on the result `(a?.b).c`, arithmetic `a?.b + 1`, `await (a?.b)()`, `new (a?.b)()`, spreading, or destructuring.\n\n## Confirmed instance (from CodeFactor)\n\n- `tests/unit/extensions/extension-command.spec.ts:5960` (col 15)\n- 25 total — see the CodeFactor list for the complete set.\n\n## Fix\n\nNot blindly auto-fixable — review each. Options: guard the result first, use non-optional access where the value is provably defined, or restructure so the optional-chain result is not consumed where `undefined` is invalid. Keep behavior identical; tests + 100% coverage + typecheck must stay green."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: code-quality,codefactor,eslint,maintainability
